        <Document ID="CD58A06E-44B0-414A-8613-88CE0BFE5FDA">
            <Title>8. Secure cloud “LLM gateway”</Title>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="2B7667DB-E075-426F-B0A1-F92E1F2A1BEA">
            <Title>Git</Title>
            <Text>✅ 5. Version Control (Very Important)
If you’re not already:
Initialize git now.
In your project folder:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Phase 1 working baseline"
Then every feature:

git add .
git commit -m "Add PDF import"
Now your memory lives in git history.
This is your real “context preservation”.

✅ 6. Optional: Branching for Safety
When experimenting:

git checkout -b feature/pdf-import
If we break something, you can go back instantly.
</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="E8280F6B-EF92-424B-BD6B-198C9A9EF9E6">
            <Text>
Product UX that keeps you out of trouble
	•	Always present the AI output as informational, not medical advice.
	•	Always show sources/citations and allow “open the original.”
	•	Provide an “Export for clinician” packet: timeline + meds + problems + key labs with citations.
</Text>
